Transposable Element Finder (TEF) - Detection of active transposable elements from NGS data

[Top Page]
TEF is a high-performance detector of active transposable elements from short-reads of next generation sequencer, based on detection of Target Site Duplication (TSD) at the transposition.
Scripts and Readme: https://github.com/akiomiyao/tef/

Detection of transposed TEs in Arabidopsis thaliana herbarium specimen

Transposed TEs have been detected from herbarium specimen of old Arabidopsis thaliana.
The history of TE evolution can be revealed by specimens kept in the herbarium.
The expansion of the territory of Arabidopsis lines can also be grasped.
  • SRA information: SRP401121
  • HB0764 (Accession Number SRR21814507) was sampled in 1905. HB0750 (Accession Number SRR21814514) was sampled in 1957.
